The bodies of three people shot dead in Kapedo on Tuesday were received at Lodwar Airstrip on Wednesday. Turkana East sub-county director of education Ibrahim Sheikh and two AP officers were killed at Lomelo by suspected Pokot bandits. Turkana county commissioner Seif Matata termed the attack heinous but noted the ambushed vehicle was not transporting KCSE examinations. Inspector John Wabwire of Kapedo AP camp said yesterday that the papers were being returned from Kapedo. Nine people were injured. Driver Amos Maina was shot in the abdomen but managed to reach Lomelo AP camp. "Ground operations are ongoing. The culprits will be arrested," Matata said, adding security was heightened in the area. Read: Three killed as bandits attack car ferrying KCSE papers in Turkana        